            . I live in <placeName id="t18240114-79-crimeloc459">Queen-street, Edgware-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240114-79-crimeloc459" type="placeName" value="Queen-street, Edgware-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240114-79-crimeloc459" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240114-79-off457 t18240114-79-crimeloc459"></join>. On 15th of January, about half-past six o'clock in the evening, I was in my parlour, and heard the top of the tobacco jar rattle in the shop. I ran out, saw two boys running away, and took the prisoner one hundred yards off - I found nothing on him. I picked the jar up as I came back. I had not seen him in the shop. I had closed the door half an hour before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240114-79-person777">
                  MARY 
                  ANN CROSSMAN
               <interp inst="t18240114-79-person777" type="surname" value="ANN CROSSMAN"></interp>
